  "prompt": "How long should a short story be?",
  "response": "The length of a short story can vary widely depending on the publication, genre, and purpose. Generally, a short story is typically between 1,000 to 7,500 words. However, some can be shorter, around 500 words (often referred to as flash fiction), while others can be longer, up to 20,000 words. Here are some common guidelines:\n\n- Flash Fiction: 500 to 1,000 words\n- Short Story: 1,000 to 7,500 words\n- Novelette: 7,500 to 20,000 words\n- Novella: 20,000 to 50,000 words\n\nUltimately, the length should be sufficient to tell a complete and engaging story, with well-developed characters and plot, while maintaining brevity and focus.",
